Key Match Events: Walker Buehler allowed one run and posted one strikeout through five innings in a playoff game for the Dodgers.
Pre-Game Insights: Fans doubted the Dodgers could win the series finale with the Padres with Buehler on the mound.

Buehler spoke about what gets him going in big games, saying 'This is a playoff game for us. The number-2 team in the division – us, kind of keeping our destiny if we win the game, we win the division – that’s what gets me going.'
Post-Match Reflections: Buehler expressed his excitement about his performance, saying 'I’m ecstatic. The team has carried me, and let me tread water for a long time, and it’s a nice feeling to have a good one.'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Dodgers clinched the National League West division, marking their 11th division title in the last 12 years.
Others: The Dodgers have overcome an unprecedented number of injuries this season and will be asked to continue jumping through hurdles in October.
